WEBVTT

00:01.167 --> 00:03.158
<i>NARRATOR: Previously on</i> One Tree Hill.

00:05.271 --> 00:06.295
Grandpa.

00:06.806 --> 00:08.273
It's time for you to get back to your life.

00:08.341 --> 00:09.740
And that all starts with a simple question.

00:09.809 --> 00:10.833
What do you want?

00:10.910 --> 00:13.378
I want to use my success to help a child.

00:13.446 --> 00:15.778
And I could be a great mother.

00:15.849 --> 00:18.147
I could help them find
what makes them special.

00:18.218 --> 00:20.982
I want to believe in it all again.
And I want Lucas.

00:21.054 --> 00:22.043
AND Y: Have you spoken with Peyton?

00:22.122 --> 00:23.555
- Since the wedding?
- No.

00:23.623 --> 00:25.352
- MAX: You think about him much?
- Every day.

00:25.425 --> 00:27.620
PSYCHIATRIST: And, Haley, you never refer
to yourself as a musician.

00:27.694 --> 00:30.720
Yeah. Yeah, well, I haven't recorded
in a really long time.

00:30.797 --> 00:34.995
What about you, Nathan? Best days ever?
Playing basketball in front of thousands?

00:35.068 --> 00:36.763
For me, yeah.

00:36.836 --> 00:39.828
- He's not worth it, okay? Let it go.
- You're lucky.

00:39.906 --> 00:43.103
You have a hairline fracture
of your right carpal radius.

00:43.176 --> 00:45.303
You need the cast on.

00:45.378 --> 00:47.403
Lindsey needs to be convinced
that you love her.

00:47.480 --> 00:50.574
And did I mention that I have a private jet,
and New York's not too far from here?

00:53.420 --> 00:57.083
I love you, too, Luke, you know that.
But I can't be with you.

00:57.157 --> 00:58.556
One of these days you're gonna wake up

00:58.625 --> 01:00.320
and you're gonna realize
how much I love you.

01:00.393 --> 01:03.920
And whenever that day is,
I'll still be waiting for you.

