01:12.639 --> 01:14.072
(RIDEPLAYING)

01:16.309 --> 01:20.177
<i>LUKE: Lindsey. She's the first thing</i>
<i>I think about every day.</i>

01:20.246 --> 01:23.340
<i>How is she?</i>
<i>Does she miss me like I miss her?</i>

01:25.251 --> 01:27.151
<i>How do I get her back?</i>

01:28.922 --> 01:31.288
<i>And then another day without her begins.</i>

01:35.562 --> 01:36.722
<i>PEYTON: Lucas.</i>

01:37.697 --> 01:42.031
<i>If I told you the reasons why</i>

01:42.102 --> 01:44.764
<i>Would you leave your life...</i>

01:44.838 --> 01:46.066
<i>JAMIE: Chester.</i>

01:54.948 --> 01:56.142
<i>BROOKE: Brooke.</i>

01:57.717 --> 01:59.548
<i>Oh, my God, I have to pee.</i>

02:03.590 --> 02:05.114
<i>SKILLS: What day is it?</i>

02:06.426 --> 02:08.018
<i>What time is it?</i>

02:08.828 --> 02:11.422
<i>What the hell did I drink last night?</i>

02:14.968 --> 02:18.062
<i>MOUTH: Millicent, you smell so good.</i>

02:19.939 --> 02:24.035
<i>I have to go to work.</i>
<i>Sure, I guess I could be a little late.</i>

02:27.247 --> 02:30.944
<i>What do you mean, I'm fired?</i>
<i>I wasn't even that late.</i>

02:31.017 --> 02:33.815
<i>How am I gonna pay my rent?</i>

02:33.887 --> 02:36.412
<i>Would you like fries with that, sir?</i>

02:46.199 --> 02:47.359
<i>HALEY: Jamie.</i>

02:48.968 --> 02:50.128
<i>NA THAN: Jamie.</i>

02:51.771 --> 02:53.534
<i>God, my girl is hot.</i>

02:54.507 --> 02:56.668
- Morning.
- Morning.

03:00.280 --> 03:01.474
(JAMIE CHUCKLING)

03:03.616 --> 03:06.312
- I'm hungry this morning.
- I'm starving.

03:07.153 --> 03:08.347
(JAMIE LAUGHING)

03:09.255 --> 03:10.279
JAMIE: It tickles.

03:12.358 --> 03:14.258
<i>(GUN FIRES)</i>

03:16.229 --> 03:17.389
<i>DAN: Keith.</i>

03:21.334 --> 03:22.596
It smells good in here.

03:22.669 --> 03:24.967
- Yeah, I made some French toast.
- Nice.

03:25.038 --> 03:27.336
- It's totally good, Daddy.
- HALEY: It's totally good.

03:27.407 --> 03:31.207
Well, that's not what I meant,
but that smells good, too.

03:31.277 --> 03:33.472
- Good morning.
- What's your day like?

03:33.546 --> 03:35.309
Mostly just playing.

03:36.849 --> 03:40.580
My day's not bad, either.
I'm just gonna finish grading these papers

03:40.653 --> 03:42.450
and then go over to see Peyton
for a little bit,

03:42.522 --> 03:46.219
and then you and I have
to interview the N-A-N-N-l-E-S.

03:46.292 --> 03:47.759
I hate it when you spell.

03:47.827 --> 03:52.389
- Don't say hate.
- Sorry, I just think it's D-U-M.

03:52.465 --> 03:56.629
Wow. Add a "B" to the end of that
or you will be, too.

03:56.703 --> 03:59.831
Jamie, what do you think about
going to practice with me today?

03:59.906 --> 04:02.636
- Can I?
- I don't know. It's a big step.

04:02.709 --> 04:04.700
What do you think, Mom?

04:07.080 --> 04:10.516
- Please be careful.
- Sweet. I'll go get my jersey.

04:10.583 --> 04:11.572
(NATHAN CHEERING)

04:12.085 --> 04:13.143
You.

04:15.355 --> 04:20.486
- Thanks, Mama, I L-O-V-E you.
- I L-O-V-E you, too, smarty-pants.

04:21.261 --> 04:22.353
You're so cute.

04:22.428 --> 04:24.020
Kid's got your brains.

04:24.097 --> 04:26.088
I just now figured out
that you were spelling "nannies."

04:26.165 --> 04:29.396
Whatever. They're getting here at 5:00,
by the way.

04:29.469 --> 04:31.300
And if you run into Quentin
at practice, will you tell him

04:31.371 --> 04:33.931
he's doing a really great job
with his chapter report on <i>Les Mis?</i>

04:34.007 --> 04:36.874
That's good. Now if only he could
figure out his jump shot.

04:37.310 --> 04:39.301
- I'll see you.
- Bye, baby.

04:48.354 --> 04:50.151
Desk looks good on you, coach.

04:50.223 --> 04:51.212
(CHUCKLES)

04:51.457 --> 04:53.550
Welcome back, Coach Scott.

04:53.626 --> 04:56.390
- So how my boy doing?
- Your boy's good.

04:56.462 --> 04:57.793
Sorry I was out of touch for so long.

04:57.864 --> 05:00.298
Hey. You gotta do
what you gotta do, right?

05:00.366 --> 05:02.425
I just wish I was able
to help you somehow.

05:02.502 --> 05:06.302
You did. You ran the team
for the last month. How they doing?

05:07.573 --> 05:10.201
You know. You win some, you lose some.

05:10.410 --> 05:11.434
Uh-huh.

05:11.511 --> 05:13.502
And how many some did you lose?

05:15.181 --> 05:18.912
- You've lost eight games?
- Yeah, but we won four.

05:18.985 --> 05:23.046
Well, three plus the first one,
but you was here for that one.

05:23.122 --> 05:25.818
Look, I know this is not
what you was hoping for.

05:25.892 --> 05:26.881
Hmm.

05:26.959 --> 05:29.484
And I'm taking all the blame for this.

05:29.562 --> 05:31.962
But I'm gonna keep it real with you.

05:32.031 --> 05:35.933
Q sucks. And it's all his fault.
I mean, he ain't hit a shot since you left.

05:36.002 --> 05:39.904
- Because they're doubling him.
- No. His hand is messed-up.

05:41.307 --> 05:44.504
I mean, we ice it constantly,
but it just ain't been right

05:44.577 --> 05:46.807
since he punched
that knucklehead over at Tric.

05:46.879 --> 05:50.747
- Well, what's Q saying?
- He said he had it checked out.

05:50.817 --> 05:53.251
All right, I'll talk to him.

05:53.319 --> 05:55.344
See, that's the thing.

05:55.421 --> 05:58.447
He asked me not to say nothing
to you about this.

05:58.524 --> 06:00.856
He think the injury gonna
cost him a scholarship.

06:00.927 --> 06:02.224
I'll tell you what's gonna
cost him a scholarship.

06:02.295 --> 06:05.162
- Playing injured and going four and eight.
- Yeah.

06:05.231 --> 06:07.722
- Let's get him in here.
- All right.

06:07.800 --> 06:10.701
- Uncle Lucas.
- Hey, there's the man.

06:12.772 --> 06:16.173
- I missed you, boy.
- Daddy said you were on a ship.

06:16.242 --> 06:19.336
- Did you see any pirates?
- Yeah, I saw a couple of pirate ships,

06:19.412 --> 06:21.972
but they didn't want any part of me.

06:22.048 --> 06:24.983
You wanna show me your jump shot?
All right.

06:25.818 --> 06:27.649
<i>(BREAK YOU</i> PLAYING)

06:27.720 --> 06:31.679
- Welcome back, Luke. You good?
- I'm working on it.

06:52.278 --> 06:53.267
Oh, my God.

06:53.946 --> 06:55.174
Oh, my God.

06:55.248 --> 06:57.910
- The Macy's presentation. I forgot.
- I remembered, it's all right here.

06:57.984 --> 07:00.782
- We just need your design sketches.
- Thank you.

07:00.853 --> 07:05.950
You have really stepped up, especially
with you-know-who out of the picture.

07:06.025 --> 07:09.358
- But...
- But what? Am I in trouble?

07:09.429 --> 07:12.728
No. I was actually thinking that

07:12.799 --> 07:16.132
you are way too valuable
to just be my assistant anymore.

07:16.202 --> 07:21.970
So how would you feel about
a little raise and a little promotion?

07:22.442 --> 07:24.967
Oh, my gosh. I don't know what to say.

07:25.044 --> 07:26.705
What's my title gonna be?
Something cool, I hope.

07:26.779 --> 07:31.580
Well, we'll figure all that out, but we
have to get you back to New York first.

07:32.652 --> 07:33.949
(PHONE RINGING)

07:35.154 --> 07:37.679
Clothes Over Bro's. This is she.

07:39.091 --> 07:40.080
Oh.

07:41.594 --> 07:42.583
Oh.

07:43.095 --> 07:46.030
No, absolutely, I can.

07:46.098 --> 07:48.794
I mean, I will. Yes.

07:51.370 --> 07:52.701
Thank you.

07:55.174 --> 07:59.611
Brooke, I'm so happy, really, but I'm not
sure I can go back to New York.

08:00.613 --> 08:04.049
That's okay. Change of plans.
I'm gonna need you here.

08:04.717 --> 08:05.979
Oh, good.

08:06.619 --> 08:08.712
Why? What's wrong?

08:11.090 --> 08:12.819
I'm gonna be a mom.

08:20.566 --> 08:21.555
Brooke, I don't understand.

08:21.634 --> 08:22.658
What do you mean
you're going to be a mom?

08:22.735 --> 08:24.100
That was the lady from the agency.

08:24.170 --> 08:26.502
The horrible woman who said she
wouldn't recommend you for adoption?

08:26.572 --> 08:30.303
She said it's like a special case,
like a foster care thing.

08:30.943 --> 08:32.876
I have to get ready
and I can't get this in my bag.

08:32.945 --> 08:35.072
Okay. First of all, you don't need this.

08:35.147 --> 08:37.842
What do you need?
What can I help you with?

08:37.917 --> 08:41.114
I don't know, I've never had a baby.
I don't know what babies need.

08:41.187 --> 08:45.248
I just... I have to go,
and I cannot get this in my bag.

08:45.324 --> 08:48.919
Once again, you don't need this.
Now just calm down.

08:48.995 --> 08:51.293
- Okay, where are my keys?
- They're in your hand,

08:51.364 --> 08:54.128
but I'm not sure you should be driving.
Let me get you some water.

08:54.200 --> 08:55.531
Millicent.

08:58.070 --> 09:00.061
They're giving me a baby.

09:07.613 --> 09:10.173
JAMIE: There's something missing.
Up on the wall.

09:10.249 --> 09:13.047
There used to be another one.
What was it?

09:13.786 --> 09:14.878
(NATHAN SIGHS)

09:14.954 --> 09:16.945
That was your grandfather's jersey.

09:17.023 --> 09:20.857
Grandpa Dan? Why'd they take it down?

09:20.927 --> 09:23.259
Because of the bad things he did.

09:23.329 --> 09:26.389
People decided
they didn't want it up there anymore.

09:26.465 --> 09:30.492
You do bad things sometimes, Daddy.
And yours is still up there.

09:32.972 --> 09:34.439
Not that bad.

09:35.174 --> 09:36.198
QUENTIN: Ho-ho.

09:36.275 --> 09:37.765
There he is.

09:37.843 --> 09:40.835
<i>(RAPPING)</i>
<i>I said it's J. Luke Scott, the boy is hot</i>

09:40.913 --> 09:43.313
<i>Wherever he goes, homey, that's the spot</i>

09:43.382 --> 09:45.646
<i>His name is Q, he's better than you</i>

09:45.718 --> 09:48.482
<i>If the spot is hot, then he's there, too</i>

09:49.121 --> 09:51.055
- My man.
- Yeah.

09:51.123 --> 09:54.024
<i>I'm the dad and I'm not so bad, I...</i>

10:00.266 --> 10:01.665
Mr. Fields.

10:03.002 --> 10:06.369
Well, well. The prodigal coach returns.

10:07.306 --> 10:08.398
Rocking a tan to boot.

10:08.474 --> 10:10.999
What's going on, Coach? You trying
to get all dark and sexy like me?

10:11.077 --> 10:12.066
(CHUCKLES)

10:12.144 --> 10:14.271
It's good to see you, too.

10:14.347 --> 10:17.316
Man, come on now, coach.
You know how we roll.

10:17.383 --> 10:19.351
Even Big Game James know that.

10:19.418 --> 10:22.012
Yeah, I know, but this is how I roll.

10:35.635 --> 10:38.263
<i>(SPITFIREPLAYING</i> ON STEREO)

10:41.207 --> 10:44.233
- HALEY: Hey, knock, knock.
- Hey, foxy, what's up?

10:44.443 --> 10:45.637
(LOWERS VOLUME)

10:47.046 --> 10:48.411
I like that outfit.

10:48.481 --> 10:51.575
Thank you. There are perks to having
a very famous designer as a roommate.

10:51.651 --> 10:53.676
You get tons of free stuff.

10:53.753 --> 10:55.618
Speaking of, check out all these demos.

10:55.688 --> 10:57.781
Wow, looks like things
are picking up, huh?

10:57.857 --> 11:02.590
Well, mostly because your instincts are
pretty kick-ass, Haley James Scott.

11:02.662 --> 11:05.722
Mia's album is killing it.
And are you ready for this?

11:05.798 --> 11:09.427
She has sold 40,000 copies.

11:09.502 --> 11:12.801
Wow, that's great. That's really great.

11:12.872 --> 11:15.102
She's really the kind of girl
that deserves it, you know?

11:15.174 --> 11:18.234
I know.
Now I just need to find another one.

11:18.310 --> 11:20.369
Well, I already did. You.

11:20.446 --> 11:23.540
You deserve all the success
you're getting and more.

11:23.616 --> 11:26.244
And I'm really proud of you.

11:26.318 --> 11:28.252
Thanks, Haley, I really...

11:28.320 --> 11:30.447
It means a lot to me, coming from you.

11:30.523 --> 11:31.854
Actually that was just to butter you up,

11:31.924 --> 11:33.653
because I really need
to ask you for a favor.

11:33.726 --> 11:37.389
You are a crack ho. What is it? Anything.

11:37.463 --> 11:39.658
So you know how you're looking
for the next great artist

11:39.732 --> 11:42.257
and you really trust
my instincts and everything?

11:42.334 --> 11:45.167
- Do you have a demo for me?
- I do.

11:45.237 --> 11:48.468
Haley, that's awesome. Who is it?

11:48.541 --> 11:50.406
Haley James Scott.

11:54.914 --> 11:56.006
Yes.

12:00.219 --> 12:03.586
Look, man, the doc says it's gonna be
a little swollen from time to time.

12:03.656 --> 12:05.920
Why you all sweating it so hard?

12:05.991 --> 12:07.959
Because we're four and eight.

12:08.027 --> 12:10.291
- Hey, maybe that's 'cause of the coaching.
- Easy.

12:10.362 --> 12:11.920
Look, I'm just saying, man.

12:11.997 --> 12:16.195
One of them disappeared for a month.
The other one can't be trusted.

12:16.936 --> 12:18.267
All right.

12:22.241 --> 12:24.675
- I want you to palm these.
- Please.

12:27.947 --> 12:31.678
- There. You happy?
- Not quite.

12:31.751 --> 12:34.242
Palm the balls and hold them there.

12:35.855 --> 12:39.689
- For how long?
- I don't know, 30 seconds.

12:39.759 --> 12:42.125
Shouldn't be a problem, right?

12:42.194 --> 12:45.288
I do this and all this nonsense goes away.

12:46.632 --> 12:48.156
Thirty seconds.

12:55.241 --> 12:58.938
You see, the thing is, Q,
it's not so much that we're four and eight.

12:59.011 --> 13:00.945
We're four and eight
and you shooting like trash.

13:01.013 --> 13:02.844
Yeah, that's 'cause they doubling me, man.

13:02.915 --> 13:04.314
Double teams never bothered you before.

13:04.383 --> 13:09.150
No, see you're one of the best shooters
I've ever seen, Q. When you're healthy.

13:10.055 --> 13:12.717
The other ones, well,
they're right here in the gym.

13:12.792 --> 13:15.920
- Even me, Uncle Lucas?
- Especially you, Jamie.

13:15.995 --> 13:19.158
See you and Quentin
are the best shooters we got.

13:22.868 --> 13:24.631
When you're healthy.

13:24.703 --> 13:26.102
(SIGHS)

13:26.172 --> 13:31.508
Nothing like a second opinion.
And this time, we'll come with you. Go.

13:50.629 --> 13:53.257
<i>(IN LOVING</i> MEMORYPLAYING)

13:54.066 --> 13:55.192
I have news, boyfriend.

13:55.267 --> 13:58.259
I might be getting a promotion
and staying in Tree Hill.

13:58.337 --> 14:01.829
I might be getting a promotion
and leaving Tree Hill.

14:01.907 --> 14:04.205
What? Why?

14:04.910 --> 14:09.244
Before I got the job at the local station,
I sent audition tapes everywhere.

14:09.315 --> 14:13.945
There's a good station in Omaha
and they saw the Ravens feature I did

14:14.019 --> 14:16.010
and they're offering me a job.

14:16.088 --> 14:18.886
- In Nebraska?
- Yeah.

14:18.958 --> 14:23.486
The nearest Clothes Over Bro's location
to Omaha is this one.

14:23.562 --> 14:25.154
Yeah, I figured.

14:26.599 --> 14:29.625
Well, is it really that much better
than where you're at, Marvin?

14:29.702 --> 14:32.330
I mean, like you said,
you've already done one feature here,

14:32.404 --> 14:34.372
- maybe you'll get to do more.
- Maybe, but,

14:34.440 --> 14:36.738
it was really just 'cause
they were in a bind.

14:36.809 --> 14:39.744
This would be a full-time on-air position.

14:39.812 --> 14:42.975
It's a small market
but it's a great opportunity.

14:44.016 --> 14:45.608
- You should take it.
- But I...

14:45.684 --> 14:48.983
If it gets you closer to your dream,
then you should take it.

14:49.054 --> 14:52.387
- I don't think it's that easy.
- Why not?

14:52.458 --> 14:55.950
Well, because
you're part of my dream, too.

14:56.028 --> 14:59.862
Millie, I know we just started out,
but I love being with you

15:00.933 --> 15:04.369
and I guess I was hoping
we had a future. Together.

15:06.672 --> 15:09.903
Oh, God, was that too early?
Did I freak you out?

15:09.975 --> 15:12.409
- Freaked you out, didn't I?
- No.

15:12.478 --> 15:16.938
There is no way those words could've
been too early. Not coming from you.

15:20.152 --> 15:22.848
Just promise me that if you do take
the job that I can have your room,

15:22.922 --> 15:27.450
because I'd really like to find
a place to stay that's not pay-by-the-day.

15:29.762 --> 15:31.354
<i>(LEA VING TOWN</i> ALIVEPLAYING)

15:31.430 --> 15:37.494
<i>HALEY: (SINGING) Life is for the living,</i>
<i>the forgiving and for leaving town alive</i>

15:41.907 --> 15:43.670
I know it's really rough,
but I was thinking...

15:43.742 --> 15:45.539
- Yes.
- But it's okay, if you wanted...

15:45.611 --> 15:48.944
Will you stop? The answer is yes, okay?

15:49.014 --> 15:51.073
I've been waiting for
the opportunity to go out and buy

15:51.150 --> 15:54.210
the next Haley James record.
So of course I want to record it.

15:54.286 --> 15:57.380
- It might be kind of fun, huh?
- Well, you did have a major label debut

15:57.456 --> 16:00.619
that did pretty good,
so it is good business for me.

16:00.693 --> 16:04.459
- But yes, it's gonna be a blast.
- Yeah.

16:04.530 --> 16:06.521
What do you say?

16:06.598 --> 16:11.092
- I say it's exactly what I need right now.
- Well, guess what? Me, too.

16:13.238 --> 16:16.002
- What?
- I mean, you never know

16:16.075 --> 16:18.805
where the next miracle's
gonna come from.

16:18.877 --> 16:20.208
(PHONE RINGING)

16:20.279 --> 16:22.372
- It's Brooke.
- Hey, Brooke.

16:22.448 --> 16:25.076
- Hey, what's going on?
<i>- BROOKE: It's a miracle.</i>

16:25.150 --> 16:28.847
Yeah, we just said that.
What, did you bug my office?

16:28.921 --> 16:31.355
- They're giving me a baby.
- A...

16:31.423 --> 16:32.447
- Hold on. Wait. What?
- What?

16:32.524 --> 16:36.392
The lady from the agency called
this morning and they're sending me...

16:36.462 --> 16:39.090
A purple monkey?

16:39.164 --> 16:41.894
- You're adopting a purple monkey?
<i>- No.</i>

16:41.967 --> 16:44.800
Not adopting and not a monkey.
I'll explain it all later.

16:44.870 --> 16:46.235
Peyton, how crazy is this?

16:46.305 --> 16:50.071
No, Brooke, honey, that's awesome.
God, Haley and I thought we had big news.

16:50.142 --> 16:52.110
<i>Why? What's your news?</i>

16:52.177 --> 16:55.840
- We're gonna make an album together.
- Oh, whatever. I'm getting a baby.

16:55.914 --> 16:58.940
I have to go, I'll call you later. Excuse me.

17:00.352 --> 17:02.343
Wow. Today's kind of fun.

17:03.489 --> 17:07.618
Listen, Q, I know it looks grim, but, hey,
you'll have that thing off by the playoffs.

17:07.693 --> 17:10.924
- Playoffs, man, we four and eight.
- Hey, we're gonna figure it out. All right?

17:10.996 --> 17:13.055
Just hang in there.

17:14.733 --> 17:19.432
Yeah, I'd like to speak to Coach Taylor.
If you don't mind. Alone.

17:20.571 --> 17:22.597
LUKE: Yeah, we'll be downstairs.

17:23.842 --> 17:26.242
Q, keep your head up, all right?

17:34.386 --> 17:36.183
- Listen, Q...
- Man, thanks for nothing, man.

17:36.255 --> 17:38.951
I trusted you, all right?

17:39.024 --> 17:41.322
I put my ass on the line
for you every single night, man.

17:41.393 --> 17:44.692
- Quentin, you needed this.
- I needed this?

17:44.763 --> 17:46.628
You know what I needed? A scholarship.

17:46.698 --> 17:49.360
I needed you to keep your mouth shut,
that's what I needed.

17:49.435 --> 17:53.838
But you went all Uncle Tom on me
as soon as Master Lucas got back, huh?

17:54.873 --> 17:58.365
You know what? When your wrist heals
and everything's okay,

17:58.444 --> 18:00.844
I'm gonna let you take that back.

18:02.081 --> 18:06.211
But for now, just consider yourself lucky.

18:19.264 --> 18:22.233
- Hi, Grandpa.
- Hi, Jamie.

18:26.472 --> 18:29.737
If you boys wanna jump me again,
now's your chance.

18:38.083 --> 18:41.519
Hey. We're not having this.

18:41.587 --> 18:45.717
- Not having what, Son?
- You following Jamie around.

18:45.791 --> 18:47.486
I've seen you, okay? Outside of the school.

18:47.559 --> 18:48.651
I've seen you driving past the house.

18:48.727 --> 18:50.388
And now you just happen
to be at the hospital?

18:50.462 --> 18:53.829
Nathan, stop.
I was in prison for a long time, okay?

18:53.899 --> 18:56.129
I was just getting a check-up.

18:57.069 --> 19:02.632
- But the truth is, I was hoping...
- No, don't. Dan, don't hope. You hear me?

19:02.708 --> 19:04.676
There's no hope for you.

19:18.423 --> 19:21.051
I guess I just don't understand.

19:21.126 --> 19:25.119
Grandpa Dan seems nice.
How come everyone's always mad at him?

19:31.003 --> 19:33.301
You love Chester, don't you?

19:33.372 --> 19:37.968
Well, what if Grandpa Dan hurt Chester?

19:38.043 --> 19:42.104
And took him away
so you could never see him again?

19:42.181 --> 19:46.618
I guess I would be really mad at him.
And sad, too.

19:46.685 --> 19:47.777
Yeah.

19:48.987 --> 19:51.478
Well, that's how we feel.

20:03.368 --> 20:06.360
I just think
that's kind of an awful thing to say.

20:06.438 --> 20:11.705
Yes, I'm mad.
Oh, you don't think I should be mad?

20:11.777 --> 20:14.837
I thought I was just gonna have
one baby in my life, but fine.

20:14.913 --> 20:16.380
I have to go.

20:17.382 --> 20:19.316
Holy cow.

20:19.384 --> 20:22.376
Stupid Owen. A little baby talk
and he totally freaks out.

20:22.454 --> 20:24.979
Well, nothing like foisting a baby
on a guy you've almost kissed.

20:25.057 --> 20:26.854
- And a confirmed bachelor at that.
- Yeah.

20:26.925 --> 20:28.654
- What'd he say?
- Whatever. He's gonna come over later

20:28.727 --> 20:32.094
and we're gonna talk about it
or fight about it, but it doesn't matter,

20:32.164 --> 20:34.564
because baby and Brooke
are gonna be fine.

20:34.633 --> 20:37.329
Yeah, I think baby and Brooke needs
a little explanation.

20:37.402 --> 20:40.030
Like, who, when and how, for starters.

20:40.105 --> 20:42.869
Okay, so the adoption agency
has this program

20:42.941 --> 20:45.501
where babies from other countries
who need major surgeries and stuff

20:45.577 --> 20:48.478
come over to the US and doctors
donate their time to fix them up

20:48.547 --> 20:49.844
and then they go home.

20:49.915 --> 20:51.314
- Oh, cool.
- That's great.

20:51.383 --> 20:53.510
It's kind of a whenever-they-can-
squeeze-you-in sort of thing

20:53.585 --> 20:57.021
and the agency had a family, that
was supposed to host the baby, drop out,

20:57.089 --> 21:01.219
so they said
this could be a great trial run for me.

21:01.293 --> 21:02.521
- When does the baby show up?
- Is it a boy or girl?

21:02.594 --> 21:05.392
- Where are his parents, the poor thing?
- And are his parents coming, too?

21:05.464 --> 21:08.729
She's a girl. And she gets here tomorrow.
Her parents don't come with her.

21:08.800 --> 21:11.394
And they didn't tell me what's wrong
with her. They're just sort of gonna

21:11.470 --> 21:14.633
hand her over and we go from there.
And check it out.

21:14.706 --> 21:18.267
I got her a purple monkey
like the one I used to have.

21:19.611 --> 21:22.239
That's so cute.
Did you get her anything else?

21:22.314 --> 21:25.408
Yeah. I got all of this stuff.

21:25.484 --> 21:28.817
- I mean, like, you know, food.
- Or, I mean, a crib?

21:28.887 --> 21:31.617
And stuff.

21:31.690 --> 21:33.885
I got a little sidetracked.

21:33.959 --> 21:37.190
Why don't we go to my house and we'll
go through some of Jamie's old things.

21:37.262 --> 21:38.286
- Really?
- Yes.

21:38.363 --> 21:39.990
- Come on, you purple monkey.
- Thanks, guys.

21:40.065 --> 21:41.589
I'm so excited.

21:42.200 --> 21:46.068
<i>(ALONG THE WA</i> YPLAYING)

21:46.238 --> 21:49.105
- Hey, what you doing?
- Looking for places to live.

21:49.174 --> 21:52.041
Well, stop. Because I found you a place.

21:52.110 --> 21:56.012
- With me. I passed on the Omaha job.
- Marvin.

21:56.081 --> 21:59.642
I feel like I'm good at what I do,
Millicent, and I'll just work hard

21:59.718 --> 22:02.209
and hope the station gives me
another shot.

22:02.287 --> 22:03.276
Are you sure?

22:03.355 --> 22:07.951
That I'm doing the right thing?
I don't know. But about us? Yeah. I'm sure.

22:09.328 --> 22:12.024
I don't want to leave you, Millicent.

22:12.097 --> 22:14.964
But you said you needed
a place to stay and I thought

22:15.033 --> 22:17.695
you should move in with me.

22:17.769 --> 22:20.636
But, I can't. I mean...

22:23.375 --> 22:27.141
Look, I know it's soon,
but you'll save a fortune on rent.

22:27.212 --> 22:31.444
And you'll get to see me every day.
I mean, what do you say?

22:31.516 --> 22:33.746
I'd like to, but I just can't.

22:36.154 --> 22:38.987
Sorry. But I'm really glad you're staying.

22:46.998 --> 22:50.525
- Haley, thank you. This is great.
- Sure.

22:50.602 --> 22:52.365
Listen, have you given any thought

22:52.437 --> 22:55.167
to how difficult it's gonna be
to give this baby up after the surgery?

22:55.240 --> 22:57.572
You know you're gonna
fall for her, Brooke.

22:57.642 --> 23:02.102
- I know. But she needs help, right?
- Yeah.

23:02.180 --> 23:05.047
- Hey, what's going on?
- Hi.

23:05.117 --> 23:08.644
- Hi, Aunt Brooke.
- Hi, best boy ever.

23:08.720 --> 23:10.415
I have a surprise for you.

23:10.489 --> 23:13.253
- What is it?
- Okay, I found the car seat.

23:14.760 --> 23:16.921
<i>I swear I'll never, swear I'll never</i>

23:16.995 --> 23:18.394
<i>Swear I'll never do this again</i>

23:18.463 --> 23:19.725
Surprise.

23:27.639 --> 23:30.199
<i>(NO ONE'S</i> AWAREPLAYING)

23:33.478 --> 23:37.175
Must've been good to spend time
with your mom and Lily and Andy.

23:37.249 --> 23:41.583
Yeah. You know, I think we all needed it.
Plus, the view wasn't too bad, either.

23:41.653 --> 23:43.883
No, I'm sure it was beautiful.

23:43.955 --> 23:46.150
<i>To an island no one's aware of</i>

23:46.224 --> 23:50.320
So, you and Haley are gonna make
a record, huh? That's great.

23:50.395 --> 23:53.387
Actually, I was meaning to ask you,
I mean, it's totally cool if you say no,

23:53.465 --> 23:56.457
but I was thinking to cut down
on studio cost,

23:56.535 --> 24:01.029
maybe I would build a small studio
in the office. But it's your space.

24:01.106 --> 24:06.271
I think that's a great idea. I mean, I'll ask
my mom, but yeah, I think it's smart.

24:09.748 --> 24:12.148
- I don't blame you, Peyton.
- Luke...

24:12.217 --> 24:15.812
- At all. For any of it.
- I feel bad for you.

24:15.887 --> 24:19.755
I feel bad for Lindsey
and I feel responsible, somehow.

24:19.825 --> 24:23.124
And I really hope that doesn't
come off as arrogant, okay?

24:23.195 --> 24:25.356
But I know this hurt you.

24:26.832 --> 24:31.929
She's coming back, Peyton.
She loves me. And I love her.

24:33.438 --> 24:36.305
- It's gonna be okay.
- I hope so.

24:37.609 --> 24:41.010
<i>So come with me</i>

24:41.746 --> 24:42.838
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

24:43.582 --> 24:44.913
It's open.

24:48.286 --> 24:50.186
<i>Come with me</i>

24:50.255 --> 24:53.190
Kid's a lot hairier than I thought he'd be.

24:54.259 --> 24:58.889
Very funny. And he is gonna be a she.
Guess you talked to Owen.

24:58.964 --> 25:04.960
- Yeah. How you doing?
- Okay. A little freaked out, but okay.

25:05.036 --> 25:06.799
- Is he with you?
- No.

25:08.406 --> 25:10.499
Weird. He's coming over soon.

25:10.575 --> 25:13.567
Actually, he's not.
It's kind of why I'm here.

25:15.480 --> 25:16.469
Oh.

25:18.750 --> 25:19.842
Okay.

25:22.954 --> 25:28.415
You know, Brooke, Owen's my friend,
and I know he's really into you,

25:29.261 --> 25:32.094
but he's just kind of always been about
his independence, too, you know?

25:32.163 --> 25:34.028
I guess I didn't know.

25:34.699 --> 25:37.224
He's just a little threatened
with all the baby stuff.

25:37.302 --> 25:39.600
Yeah, he said that on the phone.

25:39.671 --> 25:44.665
Look, did he send you over here
to talk to me? Are we in junior high now?

25:44.743 --> 25:48.201
He didn't send me over.
And he's not coming by, either.

25:49.381 --> 25:54.580
- Then why did you?
- Well, I'm taking off.

25:54.653 --> 25:57.679
Thought I'd say goodbye
and congratulations,

25:57.756 --> 26:00.884
and maybe I want to see
your face one more time.

26:03.962 --> 26:06.396
Probably why Owen's not coming by.

26:07.432 --> 26:09.491
What is that supposed to mean?

26:09.568 --> 26:12.799
Well, he probably figures if he looked
into those eyes one more time,

26:12.871 --> 26:15.704
he'll cave on the whole
independence thing.

26:17.576 --> 26:21.034
Anyways, call me if you need anything.

26:21.112 --> 26:25.515
Someone to talk to, new carpets.
I don't know, a husband.

26:26.051 --> 26:28.451
<i>Sing with me</i>

26:28.820 --> 26:30.583
I'll see you around.

26:37.862 --> 26:39.261
Hey, Brooke?

26:40.932 --> 26:43.628
Don't take the Owen stuff too personally.

26:43.702 --> 26:48.139
- I won't.
- Yeah, you will. I know how you are.

26:48.206 --> 26:52.768
But it's just a big deal. It's kids.

26:52.844 --> 26:54.106
I mean, I know it's just one,

26:54.179 --> 26:57.478
but if you really want a family,
something that's like forever,

26:57.549 --> 26:59.244
forever scares a lot of us.

26:59.317 --> 27:02.411
<i>There's a note waiting out there</i>

27:03.622 --> 27:08.719
<i>For a song no one's aware of</i>

27:10.795 --> 27:13.093
<i>No one's aware</i>

27:16.935 --> 27:20.132
- Hi.
- Hi. Can I talk to you?

27:20.205 --> 27:21.832
Sure. Come on in.

27:22.607 --> 27:24.666
What's wrong?

27:24.743 --> 27:27.439
Maybe nothing, I hope.

27:27.512 --> 27:29.946
Okay, just have a seat. What's up?

27:30.015 --> 27:33.416
Well, I think I'll stand.
Actually, do you have something to drink?

27:33.485 --> 27:36.420
Some water or an apple martini
with a cherry, if you have it?

27:36.488 --> 27:38.285
Okay, you're kind of freaking me out.

27:38.356 --> 27:40.347
Last time someone
entered the apartment like this,

27:40.425 --> 27:43.019
it was Skills
and he thought he'd killed Chester.

27:43.094 --> 27:44.118
Jamie's bunny?

27:44.195 --> 27:47.858
Yeah, but it turns out he was just like
a really heavy sleeper, apparently.

27:47.932 --> 27:50.162
Well, it's not that, it's just...

27:50.235 --> 27:52.635
I know I sort of freaked you out
when you asked me to stay here

27:52.704 --> 27:55.036
and, well, there's a reason.

27:55.106 --> 27:57.939
- Great. I knew it.
- What?

27:58.009 --> 27:59.909
I figured this was just too good to be true.

27:59.978 --> 28:02.173
There's just a reason
we can't sleep in the same bed.

28:02.247 --> 28:04.215
- Oh, no.
- What?

28:04.282 --> 28:05.874
This is like <i>The Crying Game,</i> right?

28:05.950 --> 28:07.247
- Marvin.
- Hairy back?

28:07.318 --> 28:09.309
- Marvin.
- Well, it's either that or

28:09.387 --> 28:11.787
you're completely repulsed by me.

28:18.930 --> 28:20.397
I'm a virgin.

28:22.033 --> 28:24.126
- Really?
- Yes.

28:24.202 --> 28:27.330
And considering your last gross boss-lady
hook-up, you're clearly not,

28:27.405 --> 28:31.307
- and I am just not ready to...
- How did I find you?

28:31.376 --> 28:33.640
- What?
- Such a perfect girl

28:33.712 --> 28:37.808
who's smart and sweet and so awesome.

28:39.617 --> 28:40.641
Go on.

28:40.719 --> 28:44.155
Millie, I would never
pressure you about sex, I just...

28:44.222 --> 28:47.350
- I wanna be with you.
- But...

28:47.425 --> 28:49.552
I mean, we can even get
two beds if you want.

28:49.627 --> 28:53.620
Although, if I catch you
sneaking into mine, I'm telling Skills.

28:54.666 --> 28:58.432
I am so into you and I want you here.

28:59.571 --> 29:01.198
Will you say yes?

29:03.408 --> 29:07.708
Okay. Yes. If you think it can work.

29:07.779 --> 29:09.906
It can. It does.

29:19.657 --> 29:23.684
So I see you know CPR
and you're also a lifeguard.

29:23.762 --> 29:25.593
Mmm-hmm. Yes.

29:25.663 --> 29:28.131
You ever kissed any of
the husbands you worked for?

29:28.466 --> 29:30.331
<i>(BIRTHDA YSONG</i> PLAYING)

29:30.401 --> 29:31.663
HALEY: Okay.

29:33.204 --> 29:34.228
No.

29:36.407 --> 29:40.275
Well, sorry.

29:43.314 --> 29:48.047
So Nathan, Haley tells me you like to
watch your nanny swim naked in the pool?

29:51.256 --> 29:53.156
I guess I deserve that.

29:58.129 --> 30:01.530
Hey, Brooke. You okay?

30:02.700 --> 30:07.034
- I think I made a big mistake.
- I think it's a little late for that, isn't it?

30:07.105 --> 30:09.938
If I wanted "a little late for that,"
I would've called Peyton.

30:10.008 --> 30:15.071
You are supposed to say,
"No, you didn't. You're gonna be fine."

30:15.146 --> 30:17.671
No, you didn't. You're gonna be fine.

30:17.749 --> 30:19.614
It doesn't count now.

30:20.084 --> 30:21.073
(CHUCKLES)

30:23.354 --> 30:26.619
So you got her a purple monkey, huh?
Just like you had.

30:26.691 --> 30:29.421
- You remember that?
- Of course.

30:29.494 --> 30:31.928
I do know some things about you,
Brooke Davis.

30:31.996 --> 30:35.796
- And you're gonna be a great mom.
- I'm not even going to be a mom.

30:35.867 --> 30:38.529
They'll just fix her up
and then I have to send her back.

30:38.603 --> 30:41.197
Well, if you didn't do it, who would?

30:41.539 --> 30:42.665
Hmm?

30:44.275 --> 30:47.836
Owen thinks I'm being selfish.
He thinks I just want what I want.

30:47.912 --> 30:50.073
- Well, I'd say it's the opposite.
- Right?

30:50.148 --> 30:52.673
I think it's great that you're willing
to help this little girl

30:52.750 --> 30:56.481
get the care that she needs
and get to the rest of her life.

30:56.554 --> 30:59.785
So do I.
But what if I do something wrong, Luke?

30:59.858 --> 31:03.988
What if I hurt her? What if I break her?
I mean, I rushed into this and I'm scared.

31:04.062 --> 31:05.222
Okay, you know what?

31:05.296 --> 31:09.232
When it comes to single moms,
I had a pretty special one.

31:09.300 --> 31:13.737
And it's good that you're a little scared.
But you're gonna do great.

31:16.908 --> 31:18.535
Thanks.

31:19.444 --> 31:21.378
Thanks for coming over.

31:22.814 --> 31:24.679
You think she'll like the purple monkey?

31:24.749 --> 31:25.738
(LUKE CHUCKLES)

31:27.051 --> 31:30.782
I think that she's gonna love
the girl that gives it to her.

31:32.490 --> 31:33.582
Yeah.

31:42.667 --> 31:44.601
Well, Jamie's out cold.

31:45.670 --> 31:48.400
- Wish I could sleep like that.
- Yeah, tell me about it.

31:48.473 --> 31:49.770
(SIGHS)

31:49.841 --> 31:54.005
So, sorry you couldn't find a nanny
that you could trust around me.

31:54.078 --> 31:56.569
- Too soon.
- All right.

31:58.483 --> 32:01.680
The truth is, I just want Jamie
all to myself right now.

32:01.753 --> 32:03.687
But I also want my job,
and I want my music

32:03.755 --> 32:06.223
and I want alone time with you.

32:06.291 --> 32:09.055
You should take a break from that.
Let me go through those things.

32:09.127 --> 32:13.291
I'll try to find a person that's really ugly
with a lot of great references.

32:13.364 --> 32:18.324
Actually, you can't because I thought
you might want to get a workout in.

32:18.403 --> 32:19.665
You know, our therapist said that

32:19.737 --> 32:22.638
we should focus
on the things that we love, so...

32:22.707 --> 32:24.470
I think she's right.

32:26.644 --> 32:31.206
- Probably really gonna suck, you know.
- You gotta find out sometime, right?

32:32.650 --> 32:35.448
Thank you, Hales. For everything.

32:36.187 --> 32:37.745
You're welcome.

32:39.891 --> 32:41.415
Thank you back.

32:55.206 --> 32:57.037
You lucky, man.

32:57.108 --> 33:00.202
I was gonna break that scoring title
and pull that old laundry up off the wall.

33:00.278 --> 33:03.111
Luck has nothing to do with it.
I'm just better than you.

33:03.214 --> 33:04.772
<i>(ADORE</i> ADOREPLAYING)

33:04.849 --> 33:08.376
- How you holding up?
- How you think?

33:08.453 --> 33:09.511
Somebody would've told me

33:09.587 --> 33:11.418
your old sorry ass would be
back playing before mine,

33:11.489 --> 33:14.390
I would've laughed their ass out the gym.

33:14.459 --> 33:17.189
What're you trying to do?
Make some kind of comeback?

33:17.261 --> 33:19.388
Trying to make a free throw.

33:24.202 --> 33:27.694
Yeah, let me show you how that's done,
old man. Left handed.

33:27.805 --> 33:30.467
<i>This is the song that the caged bird sings</i>

33:32.877 --> 33:36.836
You'll be just fine, Q. Even if you have
to go to a junior college first.

33:36.914 --> 33:38.711
That's what I did.

33:38.783 --> 33:41.149
Wow. And look where it got you.

33:42.920 --> 33:44.217
Let's see what you got.

33:44.288 --> 33:46.313
Hmm? Let's see what you got.

33:46.391 --> 33:48.621
Come on, Nate. Come on. Here we go.

33:48.693 --> 33:51.685
Nathan Scott. Biggest Raven of them all.
Look at you, huh?

33:51.763 --> 33:55.062
Heard they clipped your wings.
What you got, Raven?

33:56.968 --> 33:59.061
Nathan Scott. Nathan Scott.

34:01.005 --> 34:02.404
<i>Adore, adore</i>

34:02.473 --> 34:04.065
<i>Bow down before</i>

34:04.175 --> 34:05.972
<i>Bow down before</i>

34:07.345 --> 34:12.543
Just like I thought. Hmm?
They must have put salt on your tail, boy.

34:12.617 --> 34:16.576
You ain't got no chance of flying again.
Me on the other hand...

34:17.255 --> 34:18.779
<i>Bow down before</i>

34:19.357 --> 34:21.985
<i>Bow down before</i>
<i>Adore, adore</i>

34:22.060 --> 34:26.326
I could beat you with my other hand.
That ain't my shooting hand.

34:26.931 --> 34:29.592
Some comeback, Mr. Jersey-on-the-wall.

